Exploring the Cleaned Online Retail Dataset with DataExplorer

Mick Cooney mickcooney@gmail.com

Last updated: June 25, 2021

1 Introduction

We previously performed a comprehensive data exploration of the retail dataset using the dataexpks template, but now that we have removed and otherwise filtered a number of other entries from the dataset.

As these removed rows may change the visualisation of the exploration, it is worth doing a quick repeat of this exercise, so we perform those now using the DataExplorer package.

2 Load Data

We load up the cleaned dataset.

loaded_data_tbl <- read_rds("data/retail_data_cleaned_tbl.rds")

We now remove all excluded rows and run the exploration on the data with the cleaned rows excluded.

retail_data_tbl <- loaded_data_tbl %>%
  filter(exclude == FALSE)

retail_data_tbl %>% glimpse()

3 Use DataExplorer Routines

3.1 Intro Data

introduce(retail_data_tbl)
## # A tibble: 1 x 9
##      rows columns discrete_columns continuous_columns all_missing_columns
##     <int>   <int>            <int>              <int>               <int>
## 1 1015905      23               19                  4                   0
## #  with 4 more variables: total_missing_values <int>, complete_rows <int>,
## #   total_observations <int>, memory_usage <dbl>
plot_intro(retail_data_tbl)

3.2 Missing Values

plot_missing(retail_data_tbl)

plot_bar(retail_data_tbl)

plot_histogram(retail_data_tbl, ncol = 2)
